        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 12:26AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1226 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles southwest of Lake Colorado City State Park, or 19 miles
southwest of Colorado City, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colorado City Airport, Loraine, Cuthbert, Lake Colorado City,
Champion Creek Reservoir, Westbrook, Lake Colorado City State Park,
Buford, and Colorado City.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 201 and 227.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
